3. Move the k disks from auxiliary to destination using all 4 pegs

With 4 pegs available, I can use the Frame-Stewart algorithm, which is more efficient than the classic 3-peg solution. The strategy is to:
1. Move the top k disks from source to auxiliary peg using all 4 pegs
2. Move the remaining n-k disks from source to destination using 3 pegs
3. Move the k disks from auxiliary to destination using all 4 pegs

For 7 disks, the optimal k is 4. So I'll:
1. Move top 4 disks (1,2,3,4) from Peg 2 to Peg 1 using all pegs
2. Move bottom 3 disks (5,6,7) from Peg 2 to Peg 3 using pegs 2,3,4
3. Move the 4 disks from Peg 1 to Peg 3 using all pegs
